        <updateDate>2021-09-16T12:56:42Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Recovering Excessive Funds for Unused and Needless Drugs Act of 2021 or the REFUND Act of </b><b>2021</b></p> <p>This bill requires drug manufacturers to issue rebates to the Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services (CMS) in relation to discarded amounts (i.e., amounts remaining after administration) of single-dose vial drugs that are covered under Medicare. Manufacturers that fail to comply are subject to civil penalties.</p> <p>The CMS must determine rebate amounts based on payment claims from providers. (Currently, providers may receive payment under Medicare for discarded amounts of single-dose vial drugs through the use of a specific claims modifier.)</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
